                "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A branch office is treated as a permanent establishment of the foreign parent under most tax treaties. Net income earned in India is taxed at 40 percent plus applicable surcharge and education cess, the foreign company rate prescribed under the Income Tax Act 1961. GST, TDS, equalisation levy (where relevant) and transfer pricing rules (Sections 92 to 92F with Form 3CEB) also apply." }
