<!-- SECTION 4: WHO CAN FILE -->
<section class="content-section" id="who-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Eligibility and Applicability</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p>A foreign company is eligible to open a branch office in India if it meets ALL of the following conditions:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Body corporate incorporated outside India:</strong> An individual cannot apply.</li>
                    <li><strong>Profit-making track record:</strong> Profit-making during the immediately preceding 5 financial years in the home jurisdiction.</li>
                    <li><strong>Net worth USD 100,000+:</strong> Paid-up capital plus free reserves less intangible assets - not less than USD 100,000 or equivalent, supported by the latest audited balance sheet duly certified by a Chartered Accountant or equivalent in the home country.</li>
                    <li><strong>Permitted activities under FEMA Regulations 2016:</strong> Export and import of goods, professional and consultancy services, research, technical collaboration, IT and software development, technical support, representation of foreign airlines and shipping companies.</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top:16px;">A <strong>subsidiary of a financially sound parent</strong> that does not itself meet the eligibility may apply with a Letter of Comfort from the parent (LOC), subject to AD bank and RBI satisfaction.</p>
                <p style="margin-top:16px;"><strong>NOT permitted activities:</strong> Retail trading of any nature; manufacturing or processing activities directly (except in Special Economic Zones for sectors with 100% FDI); foreign legal practice; activities falling under the FDI approval route not expressly permitted by RBI in the approval letter.</p>
                <p style="margin-top:16px;"><strong>Separate AD-bank or RBI-route application required for:</strong> Sensitive sectors (defence, telecom, broadcasting, private security, atomic energy, mining of titanium-bearing minerals); applicants from countries sharing a land border with India where Press Note 3 (2020) applies. These travel to RBI in consultation with the Government of India and have longer timelines (8-12 weeks additional).</p>

            </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

