            <p class="section-subtitle" style="text-align:left;max-width:100%;">Patron's foreign-company India entry pipeline runs from discovery and eligibility review with document pack assembly (USD 100,000 net worth + 5-year profit track record + permitted activity check + Press Note 3 (2020) exposure), through Form FNC drafting with board resolution and parent certifications, AD Category-I bank submission with KYC and due diligence, RBI review and UIN allotment (4-8 weeks automatic; 8-12 weeks government route), ROC Form FC-1 filing within 30 days of approval under Section 380 Companies Act 2013, PAN + TAN + Indian rupee AD bank account + GST registration in parallel, operations launch within the 6-month statutory window and annual compliance onboarding with AAC + FC-3 + FC-4 + corporate ITR at 40% foreign company rate. Each step is a fixed deliverable - no surprises mid-engagement.</p>
