<!-- SECTION 15A: LEGAL FRAMEWORK -->
<section class="content-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Legal and Compliance Framework</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p><strong>Primary Statute:</strong> Foreign Exchange Management Act 1999 (FEMA).</p>
                <p><strong>Regulations:</strong> Foreign Exchange Management (Establishment in India of a Branch Office, Liaison Office, Project Office or any other Place of Business) Regulations 2016.</p>
                <p><strong>RBI Master Direction:</strong> RBI / FED / 2015-16 / 6, FED Master Direction No. 10 / 2015-16 (as amended).</p>
                <p><strong>Draft Reform:</strong> Draft Foreign Exchange Management (Establishment in India of a branch or office) Regulations 2025 released by RBI on 3 October 2025 for public consultation - <strong>NOT yet notified as of June 2026</strong>; 2016 framework continues to apply.</p>
                <p><strong>Companies Act Provision:</strong> Section 380 of the Companies Act 2013 + Companies (Registration of Foreign Companies) Rules 2014.</p>
                <p><strong>Application Form:</strong> Form FNC (RBI / AD bank) and Form FC-1 (ROC).</p>
                <p><strong>Annual Filings:</strong> Annual Activity Certificate (AAC) by 30 September; Form FC-3 (financial statements) and Form FC-4 (annual return) with ROC.</p>
                <p><strong>Tax Rate:</strong> Income Tax Act 1961 - 40% base rate plus surcharge and cess on net income of the branch (foreign company rate).</p>
                <p><strong>Transfer Pricing:</strong> Sections 92 to 92F of the Income Tax Act with Form 3CEB filing where transactions with the foreign parent or associated enterprises occur.</p>
                <p><strong>Profit Repatriation:</strong> Permitted on production of audited balance sheet, tax payment proof and AD bank approval (Foreign Exchange Management (Remittance of Assets) Regulations).</p>
                <p><strong>Penalty Exposure:</strong> Compounding under Section 13 of FEMA for contraventions (typically INR 2,000 to 3 times the sum involved); ROC penalties for missed FC-1, FC-3, FC-4 under Companies Act schedules.</p>
                <p><strong>Office Tenure:</strong> No general ceiling under the 2016 Regulations; 6-month window from approval to operationalise.</p>
                <p><strong>Press Note 3 (2020):</strong> DPIIT Press Note imposing Government Approval route for FDI from countries sharing a land border with India (China, Pakistan, Bangladesh, Nepal, Bhutan, Myanmar, Afghanistan); adds 8-12 weeks to BO setup timeline.</p>
                <p><strong>Regulatory Authority:</strong> Reserve Bank of India, AD Category-I Banks, Registrar of Companies Delhi, Income Tax Department (International Taxation), DPIIT and line ministry for sectoral approvals.</p>
                <p><strong>Authority for source verification:</strong> RBI Master Direction on Establishment of Branch / Liaison / Project Office at <a href="https://www.rbi.org.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">rbi.org.in</a>, Ministry of Corporate Affairs portal for foreign company filings at <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">mca.gov.in</a>, India Code source for FEMA 1999 at <a href="https://www.indiacode.nic.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">indiacode.nic.in</a> and DPIIT Press Notes at <a href="https://dpiit.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">dpiit.gov.in</a>.</p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

