<section class="content-section" style="background: var(--orange-lighter) !important; border-left: 4px solid var(--orange);">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Three Deadlines for Foreign Branch Office Setup in Delhi</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p>The FEMA Branch Office framework is unforgiving on timing. <strong>First</strong>, once the RBI approval letter is issued the branch office must commence operations in India within <strong>6 months</strong>. Failing to operationalise within this window causes the approval to lapse, and a fresh extension or new Form FNC has to be filed. <strong>Second</strong>, the ROC Form FC-1 filing deadline is HARD - <strong>30 days from the approval letter</strong>. Missing it triggers penalty under the Companies Act 2013 schedules and can cause downstream issues at PAN, TAN, GST and AD bank account opening, since these all require the FC-1 acknowledgement. <strong>Third</strong>, annual compliance is non-negotiable - AAC by 30 September each year, ROC Form FC-3 + FC-4 annually, corporate ITR at 40% foreign-company rate, Form 3CEB transfer pricing where intra-group transactions occur. FEMA Section 13 compounding (INR 2,000 to 3x the sum involved) and Companies Act penalty schedules apply.</p>
                <p>Patron Accounting builds all three into the master compliance calendar at engagement closing. The Form FC-1 filing is locked into the calendar at AD bank approval - drafted in parallel with the approval cycle so filing happens within 5-10 days of receipt, not at the 30-day edge. The 6-month operationalisation window is tracked with monthly reviews. The annual AAC + FC-3 + FC-4 + corporate ITR + Form 3CEB calendar is set at engagement closing with reminders 30 days before each due date.</p>
                <p><strong>Talk to a Patron foreign company India entry specialist in Delhi today - <a href="tel:+919459456700">Call +91 945 945 6700</a> or <a href="https://wa.me/919459456700?text=Hello%2C%20I%20want%20to%20set%20up%20a%20Branch%20Office%20of%20my%20foreign%20company%20in%20Delhi%20under%20FEMA.%20Please%20share%20the%20process%20and%20fees." target="_blank" rel="noopener">WhatsApp us</a>.</strong> Hub 12 cross-listed - indicative pricing INR 49,999 starting (BO end-to-end), INR 39,999 (LO alternative), INR 34,999 (PO alternative) (Exl GST and Govt. Charges); binding quote confirmed after the discovery call. Free first consultation. Response within 2 hours during working hours.</p>

